{
  "stem": "1901.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] early in the morning, suddenly a lot of noise, tanks, Americans.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 10 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We all on the railway station, on the-- on the-- you know, how you call it?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a normal station, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were standing there, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I never forget the name, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there, we were liberated by the Americans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The American soldiers, they-- they addressed the troops from General Patton.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were flabbergasted when they-- what they have seen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They couldn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, of course, the big mistake they made is the canned food, give us food.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's the biggest mistake they made.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I knew that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, that's-- I had a friend who was a doctor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He died the day before.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "No, he was not my friend.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we traveled quite a while together from-- he also came from Auschwitz, a Dutch-- a Dutch fellow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then on top of a tank, came an American officer, high officer, in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he said, don't touch food.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Don't come near anything-- in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You're free.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He surrounded the whole railway station.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were thousands of them, I mean-- matter of fact, we were in [NON-ENGLISH], must also have been in [NON-ENGLISH] or Feldafing-- you see the train in different parts.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There are more trains, apparently.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the Americans came virtually immediately-- I mean, half an hour later-- with the Germans use that little wagon on two wheels, and they made straightaway food for us, water, and milk were mixed here a little bit of-- of-- and they gave us something to eat.",
      "word_count": 51
    }
  ],
